rComments: Professional and fluent.
Great professor! His lectures were clear and entertaining. Though its possible to skip lectures and catch up later online, tutorial participation is mandatory.

You'll want him over all the other CS profs. Very clear cut explanations, no accents, and makes even the hard concepts easy to digest for new students. Needless to say he's got a good sense of humour. His tests and assignments are tough. You WILL want to stay on top of things to do well.

Brian is just a good lecturer overall. For B58, he starts from the atom and goes all the way to assembly in a clear manner. Each lecture is compact. The midterm was easy, but the final was tough. The labs/project can be time-consuming, but they are always the same each year. I can see why some will hate it. Practice your assembly and recursion!
This man is cool, but his tt2 was a pain in the ghand.
Very compassionate lecturer. Just be sure to pay attention class and start assignments early and the marks will come to you easily.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Amazing lectures', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Played with our emotions, made us work for it but made it worth it in the end. Don't take this course lightly, stay on top of everything. You'll think the course is easy after TT1, don't let your guard down. Our avg for tt2 was a 29% but Brian had mercy on us. Exceptional lectures, cares a lot, exceptional prof, couldn't have asked for any other!

Without the doubt, he is a great lecturer and person. He can teach everything and his humor makes you do no feel the CS is boring. Nevertheless, his assignments and exams are brutal. Better to do the assignments 1 week before the due, otherwise, you cannot stop dropping tears on the due day.
He's a great lecturer. But his assignments and exams are very difficult

He's probably the first profs for most of the CS students in university. He uses his humour and expertise to bring you into a new world/field. He challenges you every so often on assignments, exercises, and on the exams but in the meantime he also won't forget to show you that CS is fun. He's one of the most amazing profs at UofT!
Good prof, brutal exams and assignments
GOOD CHOICE

The best professor I've had yet. He's very good at explaining concepts and his lectures are never boring. I would definitely take another class with him in the future. However, his assignments and exams can be tough, but they're doable.
Hands down the best professor I've ever had.

This professor is excellent in presenting the materials to the class. His lectures are very fun. However,  some of the materials he presented weigh heavily on listening and would be hardly ever visible on the lecture slides. It is mandatory to get help from him very often since such forgotten materials do show up on the exams.

Good prof, smart guy, good lecturer and all that stuff.  Prof made our class harder than other CSC148s, so my grade is lower than people who took 148 with an easier prof. Looks bad for job applications. For amount of work I put in the course I should get "A" minimum. I got unlucky, it could have gone the other way. An ugly blemish on my transcript!

Brian Harrington is a father figure in my life. Ever since I came to the CS program, I always felt that Dr. Harrington was there for me.  He makes a lot of jokes, some good, some questionably good. Honestly probably one of the best lecturers and most engaging in UTSC.
Easy A If you attend the class, spend about 10 to 30 minutes reviewing the material every now and then. Do all the coding exercises by yourself, it will help you a lot for his MT & Final.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: This course could've been really easy but he chose to make it difficult. Ended up being surprisingly good as you weren't expected to regurgitate python syntax, but understand and be able to utilize key (basic) programming concepts. Lectures are very clear and there are many resources available to succeed in this course. Very active on piazza too!
He is a cool and funny guy. But the tests were really hard. Also, assignments and exercises were pretty hard as well.
Cool guy. Great teacher. But his assignments and exams are pretty hard unless you have good coding background.
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures', 'Test heavy', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: He is a brilliant professor. He makes the lectures very clear and interesting. The exercises are simple and just for reinforcing what we learned. Assignments and tests are a little difficult but very fair and you can do extremely well if you study. He is caring and very accessible outside of class (on Piazza, email and through office hours).
pretty nice prof, but just beware of the term tests and USE PEP8 :D

Tests are usually fair, sometimes the questions aren't very clear, overall the tests aren't very hard, but the assignments are way to long. I did get a good mark, but I think I would've get higher marks on other courses if I haven't spend so much time on this course. He also tries to be funny by telling jokes in class, but usually not very funny.
Nice teacher

Most helpful professor I have ever encountered in my life. Always keeps the course interesting, and the material relevant to real-world applications. Assignments are tough, and midterms and final even tougher. Must practice A LOT on your own to prepare, if wishing to do well in the course. Advice: Lecs and Ex's only will not cut it for this course.

Great prof very funny. Assignments and exams are pretty hard though, so be prepared to work. As long as you listen in class and are willing to spend a little extra time to really understand everything you'll be fine.
the best teacher that i have ever met!

He's a great teacher and is always willing to help students. The course CSCA08 isn't by any means easy however and could be trouble for those who haven't coded before. Assuming you are willing to put in the effort you should be able to do pretty well.
Disgustingly hard for a supposedly introductory course. Most of the time I just found myself trying to get things done despite starting on the day of assignment, not learning anything at all.

The material covered in lectures, practicals, tutorials, assignments, exercises, will not prepare you for the midterm even if you get all of them. The depth in which the midterm / final goes is insane.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Get ready to read', 'Tough grader']

rComments: My best prof at UTSC so far. He's always there for his students, overly so compared to other professors. His lectures are very organized and clear. The course load is quite hectic, so be ready to put in the work. But hey, that's CS in general. He has a sense of humour, so you'll nvr be bored in lectures. In short, gr8 prof if you're a hustler!

The best CS lecturer I had at UTSC (during the summer he taught CSC148 at UTSG). He is always there to help you out whenever you need it, very friendly and approachable and his explanations are clear and concise. However his midterm and final exam are quite challenging, but fair and his assignments are not impossible, but are brutal.
Amazing prof, very approachable. Best way to succeed in his class is to attend his lectures, review concepts and practice.
Love his lectures but both midterm and final are not easy.
He is too passionate about computer science
Someone should clone the guy and replace the rest of the professors with him!
fantastic prof!! course might not be easy but Brian is a great a lecturer. his explanations are really clear. By far the best prof!!!!!!!!!!!!!1
Loved the lectures.

Amazing prof. Super clear lectures and will go the extra mile to help you if you ask. The time from people posting a question on the question board and getting a response was around 6 minutes on average. (broke world record lol)
Good prof.
"This looks like a job for the debugger!" - Brian Harrington, 2014
By far my favourite course this semester (not the easiest though). Prof gives clear explanations and provides a lot of  helpful tools (like a peer help forum).

He suddenly became extremely hard this year, if you didn't have prior experience in programming it was extremely hard. Also did not prepare us for the midterm, everyone did terribly on it. No extensions for anything either. In my opinion he is not fit for teaching a beginners course.
Great class, awesome teacher!
I just love him! He is a very nice person and helps students in different ways!
Amazing professor.
Great guy, great class.
He is very patient about any question. Always approachable on discussion board, email and office hours. He is very nice!!! An excellent professor!!!
Great professor! Very dedicated, takes time to respond to every email and discussion board question. Very approachable.
Very good
Awesome Prof! Very helpful :)
VERY NICE PROFESSOR
